## Correctness
The new arrangement engine defines lane events, register bands, density gates, and automation curves and is fully exercised by dedicated tests. "'`build_arrangement_plan()` now returns per-scene timelines plus automation overrides, and automated tests cover sparse/medium/full lane counts, staged entry, doubles/dropouts, thinning behavior, register safety, and non-flat automation. 1975 tests pass with `pip install -e '"'.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x"'`.

## Completeness
The feature is well covered at the arrangement-model level, including staged-growth and thinning guarantees. However, the time-based timeline from `ArrangementTimeline` is not yet consumed in tracker lane-role orchestration: `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py` currently uses only `automation_overrides`/`entry_intent` from `ArrangementScenePlan`, and does not act on `lane_events` or timeline role/actions.

## Consistency
Changes are consistent with existing architecture and naming in `senseweave` and `music_tracker` (new builder is imported and used in song-plan assembly). Documentation/changelog updates appear present in the broader diff, and no regressions are indicated by full-suite execution.

## Security
No new security exposure is introduced. Identity persistence behavior is covered by existing `bootstrap_identity` tests, and startup wiring invokes `bootstrap_identity` before first-boot announcement. Identity handling remains file-based and append-only at startup.

## Quality
